<subSubSection id="528C40D2967C8C24584D5C643AFA0D03" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="137" pageId="15" pageNumber="136" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="9258990570CAD50C6BEBD1DF812E8FF5" pageId="15" pageNumber="136">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4857215601FF96D1CF8634E636CD1533" pageId="15" pageNumber="136">Japan. K. Ito s.n. (lectotype, designated here: L! [L0170980]).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA3F880F047FD0559160969363212A2B" pageId="16" pageNumber="137">
<pageBreakToken id="0E78237D29079B6EEF5D27A8A18168FB" pageId="16" pageNumber="137" start="start">In</pageBreakToken>
the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation id="B9BBD7C3A0A8CA2C5EB8770DAD130EF5" author="Blume, CL" journalOrPublisher="Museum Botanicum Lugduno-Batavum" pageId="19" pageNumber="140" pagination="1 - 25" refId="B1" refString="Blume, CL, 1849. Melastomataceae. Museum Botanicum Lugduno-Batavum 1: 1 - 25" title="Melastomataceae." volume="1" year="1849">Blume (1849)</bibRefCitation>
cited no specimen but the name &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="049B1890E51A7D3C9623C4B3A910C45E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhexia fasikan" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fasikan">
<emphasis id="8A1F5940677F95EA2BB18B658FB18B84" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="137">Rhexia fasikan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (should be 
<taxonomicName id="6298A38C14EE487A8D202E6401BD6376" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhexia hasikan" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hasikan">
<emphasis id="3E0C32A4BA137FC4C2DB43BFF21E0159" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="137">Rhexia hasikan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see below) attached to a specimen from Von 
<normalizedToken id="ECD5D8B38E405C4FFEC14AF88A23CD12" originalValue="Siebold’s">Siebold's</normalizedToken>
herbarium. Ohba and Akiyama (pers. comm.) discovered one sheet with the name &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="3F53FE0E97B91958EB713DAA46A52922" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhexia hasikan" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hasikan">
<emphasis id="81254712C6C4C5C7EDFBF6606C3584C4" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="137">Rhexia hasikan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; in the herbarium in Leiden (L0170980). The sheet contains two collections, a smaller one covered by paper on the upper part and a larger one with four branches on the middle and lower part. According to Ohba (pers. comm.), the epithet &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="D0C2F2BDA4E41916658335C52007A97A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="hasikan" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hasikan">hasikan</taxonomicName>
&quot; comes from the Japanese name of 
<taxonomicName id="272DE7A395ACE5AAF1164EAF84D5D028" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. hirsuta" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis id="2060934C3E9D494653E1B4B8D24E6B9F" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="137">B. hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, viz. 
<normalizedToken id="E3048BAA738B4387C3898633218B73AA" originalValue="“Hashikan-boku”">&quot;Hashikan-boku&quot;</normalizedToken>
. This sheet is regarded as the type material of 
<taxonomicName id="FC0AD75D90405AEF5DAE24BF74D02AE2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. hirsuta" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis id="F1EE509711B94A1D8C14806F15C52007" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="137">B. hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We here designate the larger collection on the sheet as the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="C1233131D67C30E41E9EC1F3F529375E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. hirsuta" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis id="D2BFE64AA4BA2E35ADFC82AEE10C2A70" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="137">B. hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
